text.section:
Each subwholesaler and each wholesaler:
shall get an invoice for each purchase of cigarettes;
shall keep a record of all cigarettes received, to which the subwholesaler and wholesaler shall post each day:
the invoice number;
the date of receipt;
the quantity received;
the brand; and
the name of the person from whom the cigarettes are received;
for cigarette sales to retailers:
shall keep a record of the name and address of each retailer to whom a sale is made; and
except for a transfer of cigarettes to retail stock by a written memorandum, shall prepare for each sale an invoice that shows the political subdivision where the retailer is located; and
shall keep a complete and accurate record of each sale of cigarettes to an out-of-state person for resale to out-of-state consumers.
